phases.content:
Extend `apps/desktop/src-tauri/src/github.rs` with rate-limit data types, a Tauri command to query `gh api rate_limit`, and a centralized stderr-to-user-message helper that detects rate-limit conditions in addition to the existing auth/repo errors.

### Why these three pieces together

All three are foundational and have no other dependencies â€” they're pure additions in `github.rs` plus a one-line registration in `lib.rs`. Splitting them across phases would just create artificial sequencing. Phase 2 will *use* the helper from this phase to wrap read commands; Phase 3 will *call* the Tauri command from this phase.

### Types â€” append to existing struct definitions in `github.rs`

```rust
/// One bucket from `gh api rate_limit` (core, search, graphql, etc.).
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(rename_all = "camelCase")]
pub struct RateLimitBucket {
    pub limit: u32,
    pub used: u32,
    pub remaining: u32,
    /// Unix epoch seconds (UTC) when this bucket resets.
    pub reset: u64,
}

/// Subset of `gh api rate_limit` we surface to the UI. The full GitHub response
/// includes ~14 buckets; we only render the three the desktop actually exercises
/// (core for issue/PR/label/release fetches, search for any future search calls,
/// graphql for any future GraphQL adoption).
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(rename_all = "camelCase")]
pub struct RateLimitStatus {
    pub core: RateLimitBucket,
    pub search: RateLimitBucket,
    pub graphql: RateLimitBucket,
    /// ISO-8601 timestamp the desktop captured this snapshot. Frontend can use
    /// this to age-out stale displays without recomputing from `reset`.
    pub fetched_at: String,
}

/// Helper struct for deserializing `gh api rate_limit`'s `resources` field.
/// Keeps `RateLimitStatus` clean of the wire-format wrapper.
#[derive(Debug, Deserialize)]
struct GhRateLimitResponse {
    resources: GhRateLimitResources,
}

#[derive(Debug, Deserialize)]
struct GhRateLimitResources {
    core: RateLimitBucket,
    search: RateLimitBucket,
    graphql: RateLimitBucket,
}
```

### `fetch_rate_limit_status` Tauri command

```rust
/// Query GitHub's REST `/rate_limit` endpoint via `gh api`. Returns the three
/// buckets the desktop actually uses plus a capture timestamp.
///
/// This call itself does NOT count against the rate limit (per GitHub docs:
/// https://docs.github.com/en/rest/rate-limit), so polling it from the
/// frontend is safe.
#[tauri::command]
pub fn fetch_rate_limit_status(project_path: Option<String>) -> Result<RateLimitStatus, String> {
    let mut cmd = hidden_command("gh");
    cmd.args(["api", "rate_limit"]);
    if let Some(path) = project_path {
        cmd.current_dir(path);
    }

    let output = cmd.output().map_err(|e| {
        if e.kind() == std::io::ErrorKind::NotFound {
            "GitHub CLI (gh) is not installed. Please install it from https://cli.github.com/".to_string()
        } else {
            format!("Failed to run gh CLI: {}", e)
        }
    })?;

    if !output.status.success() {
        return Err(gh_error_message(&String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stderr)));
    }

    let parsed: GhRateLimitResponse = serde_json::from_slice(&output.stdout)
        .map_err(|e| format!("Failed to parse rate_limit response: {}", e))?;

    Ok(RateLimitStatus {
        core: parsed.resources.core,
        search: parsed.resources.search,
        graphql: parsed.resources.graphql,
        fetched_at: chrono::Utc::now().to_rfc3339(),
    })
}
```

**Dependency note**: `chrono` is NOT currently in `apps/desktop/src-tauri/Cargo.toml`. Two options â€” pick the lower-risk:

- **Option A (preferred)**: use `std::time::SystemTime` + manual ISO-8601 formatting via `time` crate IF it's already a transitive dep, OR
- **Option B**: format the timestamp on the frontend side. Have Rust return Unix epoch seconds (`u64`), let TypeScript convert to ISO via `new Date(epoch * 1000).toISOString()`.

**Use Option B** to avoid adding a Rust dependency for one timestamp. Change the field to `pub fetched_at_epoch: u64` and compute via:
```rust
fetched_at_epoch: std::time::SystemTime::now()
    .duration_since(std::time::UNIX_EPOCH)
    .map(|d| d.as_secs())
    .unwrap_or(0),
```

Update the type doc-comment accordingly.

### `gh_error_message` central helper â€” add near the top of `github.rs`, below `hidden_command`

Replaces the duplicated `not logged in / not a git repository` blocks scattered across 10+ commands. Adds rate-limit detection.

```rust
/// Classification of a `gh` CLI failure derived purely from stderr text.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]
pub(crate) enum GhErrorKind {
    NotAuthenticated,
    NotAGitRepo,
    /// Primary rate limit (per-hour quota for the bucket).
    RateLimitExceeded,
    /// Secondary/abuse rate limit â€” short-lived, retry after backoff.
    SecondaryRateLimit,
    Other,
}

/// Classify `gh` CLI stderr text so the wrapper layer can decide between
/// retrying (secondary rate limits) and returning immediately (everything else).
pub(crate) fn classify_gh_error(stderr: &str) -> GhErrorKind {
    let lower = stderr.to_lowercase();
    // Order matters: secondary rate limit substring overlaps the primary one,
    // so check secondary first.
    if lower.contains("secondary rate limit") || lower.contains("abuse detection") {
        return GhErrorKind::SecondaryRateLimit;
    }
    if lower.contains("rate limit") || lower.contains("x-ratelimit-remaining: 0") {
        return GhErrorKind::RateLimitExceeded;
    }
    if lower.contains("not logged in") || lower.contains("authentication") {
        return GhErrorKind::NotAuthenticated;
    }
    if lower.contains("not a git repository") || lower.contains("no git remotes") {
        return GhErrorKind::NotAGitRepo;
    }
    GhErrorKind::Other
}

/// Convert a `gh` CLI stderr payload into a user-facing error message.
/// Centralizes the duplicated error mapping previously inlined in every command.
pub(crate) fn gh_error_message(stderr: &str) -> String {
    match classify_gh_error(stderr) {
        GhErrorKind::RateLimitExceeded => {
            "GitHub API rate limit exceeded. Wait until the limit resets (the desktop footer shows the reset time) or run 'gh auth status' to verify you're authenticated (unauthenticated requests have a much lower limit).".to_string()
        }
        GhErrorKind::SecondaryRateLimit => {
            "GitHub secondary rate limit hit. The desktop will retry automatically â€” if you keep seeing this, slow down bulk operations.".to_string()
        }
        GhErrorKind::NotAuthenticated => {
            "Not authenticated with GitHub. Run 'gh auth login' to authenticate.".to_string()
        }
        GhErrorKind::NotAGitRepo => {
            "Not in a GitHub repository. Please open a project with a GitHub remote.".to_string()
        }
        GhErrorKind::Other => format!("gh CLI failed: {}", stderr.trim()),
    }
}
```

